## 5. End-to-End Architecture

## 5.1 Logical architecture

| Layer | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| Frontend | Member checkout initiation, admin plan management |
| Firebase Auth | Identifies the logged-in user initiating purchase |
| Firestore | Stores plans, subscriptions, billing history, user access state |
| Square | Handles checkout, recurring billing, subscription events |
| Backend API routes | Starts checkout and receives webhook events |
| Lifecycle sync layer | Converts Square events into internal membership state |
| Notifications / Email | Alerts members and admins about lifecycle events |
| Analytics / Audit | Records commercial and operational history |

## 5.2 Operating principle

The integration should be treated as a **provider sync pipeline**:

1. User chooses a plan in the app
2. App validates the plan and starts Square checkout
3. Square processes payment and subscription state
4. Square sends webhook events to the app
5. App verifies authenticity and idempotency
6. App resolves the event to:
   - the correct internal plan
   - the correct internal user
7. App updates Firestore
8. Entitlements change automatically based on Firestore state
9. Alerts, notifications, analytics, and audit logs are recorded

