## 6. Environment Configuration

The current code expects these Square environment variables:

| Variable | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN` | authenticates requests to Square |
| `SQUARE_ENVIRONMENT` | chooses sandbox or production API base URL |
| `SQUARE_LOCATION_ID` | default Square location for checkout |
| `SQUARE_WEBHOOK_SIGNATURE_KEY` | verifies webhook signature authenticity |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` | used for redirect URLs |

### Recommended environment model

Use separate credentials and webhook endpoints for:

- local development / sandbox
- staging / sandbox
- production / live

### Recommendation

Never reuse production Square credentials in development or staging. Subscription systems have a nasty habit of becoming expensive the moment someone gets casual.

