## 9. Plan Management Workflow

The admin plan manager is the first operational dependency of the Square integration.

## 9.1 Admin responsibilities

Admins must be able to:

- create plan records in Firestore
- set pricing and activation state
- assign Square variation IDs
- assign Square plan IDs
- optionally assign location IDs
- activate or deactivate plans

## 9.2 Validation rules

For all paid plans:

- `billingCycle` must not be `free`
- `squareSubscriptionPlanVariationId` must be present before plan activation
- plan code must match a defined entitlement plan
- amount and billing cycle must align with the intended commercial offer

## 9.3 Operational expectation

The `membership_plans` collection is effectively the commercial catalog the app sells from. Square mappings must be treated as mandatory production configuration, not optional admin notes.

