## 10. Member Checkout Workflow

The current member-facing plan selection flow is implemented in `src/app/membership/subscribe/page.tsx`.

## 10.1 User journey

1. Authenticated member opens the subscription page
2. App loads active plans from Firestore
3. Member selects a plan
4. App retrieves the Firebase ID token
5. App calls `/api/square/create-subscription-checkout`
6. Backend validates the plan
7. Backend asks Square to create a checkout/payment link
8. Backend returns the link URL
9. Browser redirects the member to Square-hosted checkout

## 10.2 What the frontend is responsible for

- displaying only active plans
- preventing checkout if user is not authenticated
- sending authenticated request to backend
- redirecting to Square upon successful response
- displaying user-friendly failure messages

## 10.3 What the backend checkout route is responsible for

The checkout route currently performs these functions:

- verifies user authentication
- reads the requested plan from Firestore
- builds a normalized `MembershipPlan` object
- validates the plan for paid Square checkout
- resolves the Square location ID
- records analytics events for upgrade/checkout started
- creates a Square payment link
- returns the hosted checkout URL

