## 11. Checkout Route Design

## 11.1 Route

`POST /api/square/create-subscription-checkout`

## 11.2 Input contract

```json
{
  "planId": "firestore-plan-id"
}
```

## 11.3 Authentication model

The route requires a valid Firebase-authenticated user and uses the backend auth context to resolve:

- `userId`
- `role`

## 11.4 Current validation performed

The route currently checks:

- request is authenticated
- `planId` exists in the request body
- plan exists in Firestore
- plan is active
- plan is not free
- plan has a Square subscription variation mapping
- location can be resolved

## 11.5 Recommended enhancement: create a pre-checkout session record

Before calling Square, the route should write a `checkout_sessions` record.

### Recommended fields

| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `userId` | requesting user |
| `planId` | internal plan |
| `membershipPlanCode` | normalized plan code |
| `squareCustomerId` | linked provider customer if known |
| `idempotencyKey` | provider request correlation |
| `provider` | `square` |
| `status` | initiated / redirected / completed / failed |
| `createdAt` | traceability |

This gives support and operations a reliable trail when payment and membership state diverge.

