## 12. Square Customer Strategy

This is the biggest operational requirement in the full design.

## 12.1 Required behavior

Every paying user should have a persistent `squareCustomerId` stored on their Firestore `users/{uid}` document.

## 12.2 Why it matters

The webhook processor resolves the user by searching `users` on `squareCustomerId`.

If the user does not have a stored Square customer ID before billing events arrive, the app cannot reliably attach the subscription lifecycle to the correct member.

## 12.3 Recommended implementation

Before creating checkout:

1. load the user document
2. check if `squareCustomerId` exists
3. if not, create or fetch a Square customer
4. write `squareCustomerId` back to the user document
5. include that customer ID in the Square checkout payload

## 12.4 Recommended helper

Create a dedicated helper such as:

- `src/lib/square-customers.ts`

### Recommended functions

- `getOrCreateSquareCustomer(user)`
- `findSquareCustomerByEmail(email)`
- `persistSquareCustomerId(userId, squareCustomerId)`

## 12.5 Operational rule

No paid subscription flow should proceed without a reliable Square customer linkage.

