## 16. Internal Lifecycle Normalization

The lifecycle synchronizer is in `src/lib/membership-lifecycle.ts`.

It normalizes provider events into stable internal lifecycle classes.

## 16.1 Lifecycle types used by the application

| Lifecycle Type | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `subscription_created` | first successful active subscription state |
| `subscription_updated` | non-terminal subscription change |
| `subscription_canceled` | cancellation state |
| `subscription_reactivated` | reactivation or resumed access |
| `subscription_expired` | unpaid, deactivated, or lapsed state |
| `payment_succeeded` | successful payment event |
| `payment_failed` | failed payment event |
| `promotion_granted` | non-Square access grant |
| `promotion_expired` | non-Square grant expiry |

## 16.2 Status normalization

Square status values are normalized into internal membership statuses such as:

- `active`
- `pending`
- `canceled`
- `paused`
- `lapsed`
- `unpaid`
- `past_due`

## 16.3 Why this matters

The rest of the app should reason over normalized internal states, not provider-specific vocabulary.

