## 18. Alerts, Notifications, Analytics, and Audit

The Square integration is not complete unless billing changes create operational visibility.

## 18.1 Member alerts

The lifecycle layer already supports member alerts such as:

- payment failed
- subscription canceled
- subscription reactivated
- membership expiring / expired

These alerts should create:

- member notification records
- email sends
- analytics records

## 18.2 Admin alerts

Admin alerts should be generated for:

- failed payments
- billing anomalies
- webhook-processing failures
- email delivery failures related to membership alerts

## 18.3 Audit logging

Membership and billing changes should create audit entries that explain:

- what changed
- which user it affected
- what the previous and next states were
- whether the source was provider sync, admin action, or automated system behavior

## 18.4 Analytics events

The integration already logs events around upgrade and checkout start. Extend this to cover:

- checkout link created
- checkout abandoned if detectable
- subscription activated
- subscription renewed
- payment failed
- subscription canceled

