## 21. Failure Modes the Integration Must Handle

A production billing integration must be designed around unpleasant reality, not best-case demos.

## 21.1 Missing plan mapping

### Failure
A paid plan has no Square variation ID.

### Required behavior
- checkout request fails fast
- admin sees explicit error
- plan cannot be sold until mapping is fixed

## 21.2 Missing location configuration

### Failure
Neither plan nor environment provides a location ID.

### Required behavior
- checkout request fails
- no attempt is made to create a provider checkout link

## 21.3 Missing Square customer linkage

### Failure
Webhook arrives but no user can be found by `squareCustomerId`.

### Required behavior
- event is still recorded in history / anomaly logs
- event is flagged for admin investigation
- user access is not silently mutated against the wrong member

## 21.4 Duplicate webhook

### Failure
Square retries an already-processed event.

### Required behavior
- event is recognized from `square_webhook_events`
- processing exits safely
- no duplicate writes or duplicate alerts occur

## 21.5 Out-of-order webhook arrival

### Failure
A later event arrives before an earlier state transition.

### Required behavior
- lifecycle sync should use status-aware logic and timestamps where possible
- billing history remains immutable
- current subscription/user state should reflect the latest valid known truth

## 21.6 Payment failure

### Failure
Subscription charge fails.

### Required behavior
- `lastPaymentStatus` becomes failed
- lifecycle class becomes `payment_failed`
- member alert is generated
- admin alert is generated
- entitlement behavior follows your business rule for grace period vs immediate restriction

## 21.7 Signature verification failure

### Failure
Webhook signature is invalid.

### Required behavior
- request is rejected with 401
- no event processing occurs

