## 22. Security Model

## 22.1 Checkout security

The checkout route must remain server-side and authenticated. The client should never call Square directly with secret credentials.

## 22.2 Webhook security

Webhook signature verification is mandatory.

## 22.3 Secret management

The following must remain server-only:

- `SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN`
- `SQUARE_WEBHOOK_SIGNATURE_KEY`

## 22.4 Trust boundaries

| Component | Trust Level |
|---|---|
| Member browser | untrusted |
| App backend | trusted |
| Square webhook with verified signature | trusted provider input |
| Firestore user state after sync | internal source of truth |

