## 26. End-to-End Example: Successful Subscription Purchase

1. user logs in through Firebase Auth
2. user opens subscription page
3. app loads active paid plans from Firestore
4. user chooses `standard_monthly`
5. frontend sends authenticated request to `/api/square/create-subscription-checkout`
6. backend validates the plan and resolves location
7. backend creates or retrieves `squareCustomerId`
8. backend writes `checkout_sessions` record
9. backend asks Square to create hosted checkout
10. user is redirected to Square
11. user completes purchase
12. Square creates/updates subscription state
13. Square sends webhook to `/api/square/webhooks`
14. app verifies signature
15. app checks idempotency
16. app resolves plan and user
17. app normalizes lifecycle to `subscription_created` or `payment_succeeded`
18. app updates:
    - `subscriptions`
    - `users`
    - `billing_history`
    - `membership_history`
19. app generates analytics and audit records
20. app sends confirmation/notification flows as configured
21. entitlement checks now treat the user as Standard

---

## 27. End-to-End Example: Failed Renewal Payment

1. Square attempts recurring renewal payment
2. payment fails
3. Square sends payment-related webhook
4. app verifies signature and checks idempotency
5. app resolves user and subscription
6. lifecycle normalizes to `payment_failed`
7. user document updates `lastPaymentStatus = failed`
8. billing history records the failure
9. membership history records state change if applicable
10. member receives payment-failed alert
11. admin receives operational alert
12. entitlement behavior follows your configured rule for grace period or suspension

