## 30. Final Operating Model

When implemented correctly, Square should function in this application as follows:

- **Firestore plan records** define what can be sold
- **member checkout UI** initiates a purchase request
- **backend checkout logic** creates secure Square checkout links
- **Square** collects payment and manages recurring billing
- **Square webhooks** report lifecycle changes back to the app
- **billing and lifecycle sync logic** converts provider events into internal state
- **Firestore** becomes the authoritative operational record of membership
- **entitlement logic** grants or removes access across the platform
- **notifications, analytics, and audit** provide visibility and governance

That is the complete intended model.

Square is not just a payment button here. It is the external billing engine in a broader membership operating system, and it only works properly when identity, plan mapping, lifecycle sync, alerts, audit, and access control are all wired together as one pipeline.


